                        <head>86. Summary of Conclusions of a Washington Special Actions Group
                                Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d86fn1">Source: National
                                Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                                Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box
                                H–117, Washington Special Actions Group, <gloss target="#t_WSAG_1">WSAG</gloss> Minutes (Originals) 7–27–72 to 9–20–73. Top
                                Secret; Sensitive. The meeting took place in the White House
                                Situation Room. The minutes of the meeting are attached.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" from="1972-11-02T15:07:00-05:00" to="1972-11-02T16:15:00-05:00">November 2, 1972, 3:07–4:15 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline></opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Steps for the Implementation of a Southeast Asia Agreement</item>
                        </list>
