                        <pb facs="0392" n="349" xml:id="pg_349"/>
                        <p rend="center">SUMMARY OF CONCLUSIONS</p>
                        <p>It was agreed that: <list>
                                <item>—We will use civilians for as many of the intelligence
                                    functions as possible, leaving the military, including attachés,
                                    to handle strictly military functions.</item>
                                <item>—The marine guards at Embassy Saigon will not be counted as
                                    part of the fifty military personnel we will be permitted to
                                    have in Vietnam.</item>
                                <item>—The State Department will make plans for a separate
                                    international conference to establish a voluntary consultative
                                    group to consider the economic program for IndoChina.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
